The official [Android Codelabs](https://www.google.com/search?q=https://developer.android.com/codelabs) are structured so that they introduce these functions **only when you need them**.

Instead of searching for a list of 30, **do the Codelabs.** When you encounter `notifyDataSetChanged()` in a Codelab, *that* is the exact moment to pause, read the documentation for it, and experiment with it.

